==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*smiþaz''.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''[[smith]]'', Old Saxon ''-smið'' (Dutch ''[[smid]]''), Old High German ''[[smid]]'' (German ''[[Schmied]]''), Old Norse ''[[smiðr]]'' (Swedish ''[[smed]]''), Gothic [[𐌰𐌹𐌶𐌰𐍃𐌼𐌹𐌸𐌰]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/smiθ/}}

